> This luxurious dish is the definition of umami. Melt-in-your-mouth beef
> tenderloin served on top of chewy couscous swirled with black truffle butter
> and Parmesan, then topped with a creamy mustard sauce. On the side, there
> are crispy-edged roasted green beans.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a
#medium pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil. Wash and dry all produce.
Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim
@green beans{6%oz}, if necessary.

Once water is boiling, add @Israeli couscous{1/2%cup} to #pot{}. Cook until
al dente, ~{6-8%minutes}. Drain and place empty pot over medium heat. Add
@truffle butter{2%tbsp} and scallion whites; cook, stirring, until softened,
~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in cooked couscous until evenly coated. Turn off heat;
cover until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{};
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Sprinkle with half the
@bold & savory steak spice{1%tbsp} (use all for 4 servings), pressing
to adhere. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a
#large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook until a crust forms,
~{2-3%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; wipe out pan.

Transfer seared beef to one side of a #baking sheet{}. Toss green beans on
opposite side of sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper.
Roast on top rack until green beans are browned and tender and beef reaches
desired doneness, ~{10-12%minutes}. Remove from oven; let beef rest for
~{5%minutes}.

> TIP: Beef may finish before green beans.

Meanwhile, heat pan used for beef over medium-high heat. Stir in
@water{1/4%cup} (⅓ cup for 4 servings) and @beef stock concentrate{1}. Simmer
until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Reduce heat to low and whisk in
@Dijon mustard{2%tsp}. Turn off heat; stir in @sour cream{2%tbsp} and any
resting juices from beef. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If sauce gets too thick, stir in hot water 1 TBSP at a time.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}, then stir in @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and half
the scallion greens. Season with salt and pepper. Divide couscous, green
beans, and beef between plates. Spoon sauce over beef. Sprinkle with
remaining scallion greens and serve.